\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
answer 
\end_layout

\end_inset

This is a simple Diophantine equation,
 there exist 
\begin_inset Formula $n,m\in\mathbb{Z}$
\end_inset

 such that
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
x=3n+2=5m+3,
\]

\end_inset

so 
\begin_inset Formula $3n-5m=1$
\end_inset

